Preface: "Sustainable Management and Restoration of Degraded Landscapes for Achieving
Land Degradation Neutrality (LND) in India is a project of the Government of India for environment, forest and climate change management.
Global Environment Facility (GEF) in partnership with the Ministry of Climate Change and UNDP
Funding is being provided by them. The objective of the project is sustainable land in various terrains.
To promote management practices so that the damaged ecosystem and its requirements are met.
Services will be restored, poverty will be reduced, biodiversity will be protected, and climate change will be addressed.
Flexibility will increase. The project is located in Nandurbar and Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar districts of Maharashtra.
is being implemented. 3,000 hectares of forest / grassland in project implementation phase in Maharashtra
And the idea is to restore 30,000 hectares of arable land. Read No. India 2.
